The paper introduces a new model for efficient topological data structures for simplicial and cell complexes, which suggests it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the scalability of the model to high-dimensional and large-size complexes, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper introduces a concrete realization of the model for spatially embedded complexes, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or other sub-categories related to spatial data structures.
